reviewText: She's adorable, and they have a great chemistry.  I thought the third scene was a bit weak, though.  It almost seemed like she didn't get as much as she needed/wanted.
It may get off to a slow start, but good quality visual media in this genre is hard to come by, and Keith Jones and Co. does not fail to deliver.
i love this man, he is so real and so good at what he does. The actress was great, and the way she went to him at the end and fell into his arms was priceless.
